From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: OctaneOS <noreply@octaneos.local>
Date: Wed, 04 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] cpufreq: sun50i: add allwinner,sun60i-a733 to match list

The Allwinner A733 (sun60iw2) uses the same EFUSE-based OPP selection
mechanism as the H6. Without this match entry the driver never loads,
cpufreq-dt cannot select the correct OPP table grade (vf0000 vs vf0001),
and all CPUs run at the U-Boot frequency.

If the BSP provides its own A733 cpufreq driver via bsp/drivers/cpufreq/,
this patch has no effect (the BSP driver takes precedence).

Signed-off-by: OctaneOS <noreply@octaneos.local>
---
 drivers/cpufreq/sun50i-cpufreq-nvmem.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/cpufreq/sun50i-cpufreq-nvmem.c b/drivers/cpufreq/sun50i-cpufreq-nvmem.c
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/drivers/cpufreq/sun50i-cpufreq-nvmem.c
+++ b/drivers/cpufreq/sun50i-cpufreq-nvmem.c
@@ -163,6 +163,7 @@ static int __exit sun50i_cpufreq_nvmem_remove(struct platform_device *pdev)

 static const struct of_device_id sun50i_cpufreq_match_list[] = {
 	{ .compatible = "allwinner,sun50i-h6" },
+	{ .compatible = "allwinner,sun60i-a733" },
 	{}
 };
 MODULE_DEVICE_TABLE(of, sun50i_cpufreq_match_list);
